1604034000.title: Bargain Hunt
1604034000.descr: Today's Bargain Hunters are at the Quayside Antiques centre in Topsham near Exeter. Natasha Raskin Sharp presents with experts Danny Sebastian & Gary Pe on hand. Natasha also hears about HMS Terror, a local ship built in Topsham in 1813, a ship of adventure that penetrated the artic and antartic poles.

1604036700.title: Only Fools and Horses
1604036700.descr: Only Fools and Horses tells the story of two brothers, Derek (David Jason) and his sibling Rodney (Nicholas Lyndhurst), street market traders who dream of getting rich. Derek fancies himself as a ladies' man, but his attempts at passing himself off as a sophisticated jet-setter lead to hilarious misunderstandings. Younger brother Rodney is better educated, but seems destined to spend his life as Derek's look-out, and so scuppering his chances of finding a girlfriend.

1604040300.title: The Coroner
1604040300.descr: British drama. Jane Kennedy left her hometown of Lighthaven when she was a teenager. Now she is a mother of a 15-year-old daughter herself and is returning to Lighthaven to take on the role of coroner. She investigates a whole manner of mysterious, sudden, and unexplained deaths. A job which requires her to work closely with the man who broke her heart all those years ago. Starring Claire Goose and Matt Bardock.

1604043000.title: Atlantis
1604043000.descr: One day Jason wakes up on an island where there are demigods and other mythological creatures. He meets Hercules and learns that he is in Atlantis. The two are joined by the highly intelligent Pythagoras. The three of them roam the countryside and meet creatures like Medusa or the Furies. Not infrequently, the three adventurers must defend themselves against evil forces.

1604045700.title: Impossible
1604045700.descr: Entertaining and educational British quiz show, hosted by Rick Edwards, where 24 regular contestants compete throughout the series to answer tricky questions. But some of the optional answers are designed to be ''impossible'', or at the very least inconsistent with the information given. The participants must avoid selecting these booby trap answer and the best one wins the £10,000 jackpot.

1604087400.title: Doctor Who
1604087400.descr: Earth has been invaded and Bill is living alone, an isolated figure surviving in occupied Britain. The Doctor is imprisoned, and appears to be on the side of the enemy, flooding the airwaves with fake news. Bill and Nardole must embark on a deadly mission to rescue the Doctor and lead the resistance against the new regime, whatever the cost…

1604090100.title: The Room at the Top
1604090100.descr: John Braine's 1957 novel in a two-part BBC adaptation charting the rise of a young man of humble birth in post-war Britain. Targeting a high-paid job and the social status this will bring, it shows the trials and tribulations of Joe Lampton as he attempts to sweet talk and seduce his way to the social posiiton he yearns. But single-minded selfishness and drive will eventually lead to tragedy.

1604096100.title: Bad Move
1604096100.descr: Steve (Jack Dee) and Nicky (Kerry Godliman) decide to move from Leeds to the countryside of Yorkshire, where they want to live a perfect, simple life away from the rat race. Soon they find out that the reality is more than disappointing. The house is in a bad condition, the internet doesn't reach, they miss many amenities of every day life. And the neighbours can be really annoying.

1604097600.title: Friday Night Dinner
1604097600.descr: A family comedy about a Jewish family who meet for dinner every Friday night. The family includes mother Jackie, father Martin, and two sons Adam (Simon Bird) and Jonathan. The episodes consist of disruptions to the dinner by Adam and Jonathan arguing or by neighbor Jim Bell (Mark Heap.) It began just a year after the show The Inbetweeners finished, and worked as a new series for fans to watch.
